# Windsurf Configuration
- Primary Rules: Follow all instructions in `.claude/rules/`.
- Project Context: This is the `trading-control` Python project.
- Standards: Prioritize the Clean Code and Safety rules defined in your Claude setup.

## Key Project Rules from .claude/rules/

### CI/CD Requirements (from .claude/rules/memory-cicd.md)
- Always run `ruff check . --fix` before commits
- Use `ruff format --check .` for formatting validation
- Include `schema_version="v3"` in all database writes
- Test files must follow pattern: `tests/test_{module_name}.py`
- No print statements or hardcoded URLs in production code

### Trading System Rules (from .claude/rules/memory-trading.md)
- ALWAYS use `ALPACA_PAPER=true` during development
- Every order requires unique `client_order_id` with trace_id
- Redis is the source of truth for positions and orders
- Max 5% portfolio risk per trade, 10% per symbol
- Use SafeWriter for all order database operations

## Development Standards
- Python FastAPI backend with async/await patterns
- React frontend with TypeScript
- PostgreSQL database with SQLAlchemy
- Redis for real-time state management
- Structured logging with `log_structured()`

## Safety & Error Handling
- Wrap all Alpaca calls in try/except for `AlpacaAPIError`
- Use exception chaining with `raise ... from None`
- Implement exponential backoff for network retries
- Validate all external inputs and market data

## Project Structure
- `api/` - FastAPI backend code
- `frontend/` - React TypeScript frontend  
- `tests/` - Pytest test suite
- `.claude/` - Claude Code rules and memory
- `docs/` - Project documentation
